com.ibm.team.process.common

Interface IDevelopmentLineConfiguration


  • public interface IDevelopmentLineConfiguration
    Representation of an configuration of a development line. Development line configurations define the process which applies to team areas that belong to an associated development line.
    Since:
    0.5

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String getId()
      Returns the id of the development line that this configuration configures or null if no id has been specified.
      IIterationConfiguration[] getIterations()
      Returns the configured iterations within this development line, if any.

    • Method Detail

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        Returns the id of the development line that this configuration configures or null if no id has been specified.

        In order for this configuration to be saved to the repository this field must have a non-null value, so it is safe to assume that this method will not return null if it comes from a model built from an immutable item fetched from the repository. It is possible for an incomplete/invalid configuration, however, to return null.

        Returns:
        the id of this development line or null

      • getIterations

        IIterationConfiguration[] getIterations()
        Returns the configured iterations within this development line, if any.
        Returns:
        the configured iterations within this development line
